Note:
MULTI SET - Bag / Counter Tier 0 Primitive

This file implements a multi-set (a.k.a. "bag" or Python Counter) using
a chained hash table whose entries store a value and a count. Repeated
insertion increments the count rather than allocating a new entry.

Entry structure (24 bytes):
  offset 0:  value (8 bytes)
  offset 8:  count (8 bytes)
  offset 16: chain next (8 bytes)

Header (32 bytes):
  offset 0:  buckets pointer
  offset 8:  capacity
  offset 16: distinct_count (number of distinct values)
  offset 24: total_count (sum of all counts)
:End Note

Import "compiler/frontend/primitives/memory/layout.runa" as Layout
Import "compiler/frontend/primitives/core/memory_core.runa" as Memory

Let MSET_ENTRY_SIZE be 24
Let MSET_HEADER_SIZE be 32
Let MSET_INITIAL_CAPACITY be 16

@Reasoning
splitmix64 mix on value.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation
Same routine used elsewhere.
@End Implementation

@Performance_Hints
Time: O(1).
@End Performance_Hints

@Security_Scope
Non-cryptographic.
@End Security_Scope
Process called "mset_hash" takes v as Integer returns Integer:
    Let h be v
    Set h to h bitwise xor (h shifted right by 33)
    Set h to h multiplied by 18397679294719823053
    Set h to h bitwise xor (h shifted right by 33)
    Set h to h multiplied by 14181476777654086739
    Set h to h bitwise xor (h shifted right by 33)
    If h is less than 0:
        Set h to 0 minus h
    End If
    Return h
End Process

@Reasoning
Create empty multi-set.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation
Allocate header + bucket array.
@End Implementation

@Performance_Hints
Time: O(capacity).
@End Performance_Hints

@Security_Scope
Returns 0 on allocation failure.
@End Security_Scope
Process called "mset_create" returns Integer:
    Let ms be proc allocate from Layout with MSET_HEADER_SIZE
    If ms is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    Let bytes be MSET_INITIAL_CAPACITY multiplied by 8
    Let buckets be proc allocate from Layout with bytes
    If buckets is equal to 0:
        proc deallocate from Layout with ms
        Return 0
    End If
    Let zi be 0
    While zi is less than bytes:
        proc memory_set_byte from Memory with buckets, zi, 0
        Set zi to zi plus 1
    End While
    proc memory_set_int64 from Memory with ms, 0, buckets
    proc memory_set_int64 from Memory with ms, 8, MSET_INITIAL_CAPACITY
    proc memory_set_int64 from Memory with ms, 16, 0
    proc memory_set_int64 from Memory with ms, 24, 0
    Return ms
End Process

@Reasoning
Free all entries and the multi-set.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation
Walk each bucket chain freeing entries, then free buckets + header.
@End Implementation

@Performance_Hints
Time: O(n + capacity).
@End Performance_Hints

@Security_Scope
Caller-owned.
@End Security_Scope
Process called "mset_destroy" takes ms as Integer returns Integer:
    If ms is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    Let buckets be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with ms, 0
    Let capacity be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with ms, 8
    Let i be 0
    While i is less than capacity:
        Let head_addr be buckets plus (i multiplied by 8)
        Let cur be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with head_addr, 0
        While cur is not equal to 0:
            Let nx be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with cur, 16
            proc deallocate from Layout with cur
            Set cur to nx
        End While
        Set i to i plus 1
    End While
    If buckets is not equal to 0:
        proc deallocate from Layout with buckets
    End If
    proc deallocate from Layout with ms
    Return 1
End Process

@Reasoning
Find entry for value; return entry pointer or 0.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation
Hash, walk chain comparing value.
@End Implementation

@Performance_Hints
Time: O(1) average.
@End Performance_Hints

@Security_Scope
Internal helper.
@End Security_Scope
Process called "mset_find" takes ms as Integer, value as Integer returns Integer:
    Let buckets be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with ms, 0
    Let capacity be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with ms, 8
    Let mask be capacity minus 1
    Let h be proc mset_hash with value
    Let idx be h bitwise and mask
    Let head_addr be buckets plus (idx multiplied by 8)
    Let cur be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with head_addr, 0
    While cur is not equal to 0:
        Let v be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with cur, 0
        If v is equal to value:
            Return cur
        End If
        Set cur to proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with cur, 16
    End While
    Return 0
End Process

@Reasoning
Add one occurrence of value. If new, allocate entry and link into
bucket chain; otherwise increment existing entry's count.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation
1) Find existing entry. If found, increment count.
2) Else allocate new entry with count = 1, link at bucket head,
   increment distinct_count.
3) Increment total_count.
@End Implementation

@Performance_Hints
Time: amortized O(1).
@End Performance_Hints

@Security_Scope
Returns 0 on allocation failure.
@End Security_Scope
Process called "mset_add" takes ms as Integer, value as Integer returns Integer:
    If ms is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    Let existing be proc mset_find with ms, value
    If existing is not equal to 0:
        Let cnt be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with existing, 8
        proc memory_set_int64 from Memory with existing, 8, cnt plus 1
    Otherwise:
        Let entry be proc allocate from Layout with MSET_ENTRY_SIZE
        If entry is equal to 0:
            Return 0
        End If
        proc memory_set_int64 from Memory with entry, 0, value
        proc memory_set_int64 from Memory with entry, 8, 1
        Let buckets be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with ms, 0
        Let capacity be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with ms, 8
        Let mask be capacity minus 1
        Let h be proc mset_hash with value
        Let idx be h bitwise and mask
        Let head_addr be buckets plus (idx multiplied by 8)
        Let existing_head be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with head_addr, 0
        proc memory_set_int64 from Memory with entry, 16, existing_head
        proc memory_set_int64 from Memory with head_addr, 0, entry
        Let dc be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with ms, 16
        proc memory_set_int64 from Memory with ms, 16, dc plus 1
    End If
    Let tc be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with ms, 24
    proc memory_set_int64 from Memory with ms, 24, tc plus 1
    Return 1
End Process

@Reasoning
Return the multiplicity (count) of a value. Zero if absent.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation
Find entry; return count field.
@End Implementation

@Performance_Hints
Time: O(1) average.
@End Performance_Hints

@Security_Scope
Read-only.
@End Security_Scope
Process called "mset_count" takes ms as Integer, value as Integer returns Integer:
    If ms is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    Let e be proc mset_find with ms, value
    If e is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    Return proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with e, 8
End Process

@Reasoning
Remove one occurrence of value. If count reaches 0, unlink and free
the entry; decrement distinct_count.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation
Walk bucket chain. On match: decrement count. If new count is 0,
unlink entry from chain, free it, decrement distinct_count.
Decrement total_count.
@End Implementation

@Performance_Hints
Time: O(1) average.
@End Performance_Hints

@Security_Scope
Returns 0 if absent.
@End Security_Scope
Process called "mset_remove" takes ms as Integer, value as Integer returns Integer:
    If ms is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    Let buckets be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with ms, 0
    Let capacity be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with ms, 8
    Let mask be capacity minus 1
    Let h be proc mset_hash with value
    Let idx be h bitwise and mask
    Let head_addr be buckets plus (idx multiplied by 8)
    Let prev be 0
    Let cur be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with head_addr, 0
    While cur is not equal to 0:
        Let cv be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with cur, 0
        If cv is equal to value:
            Let cnt be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with cur, 8
            Let new_cnt be cnt minus 1
            proc memory_set_int64 from Memory with cur, 8, new_cnt
            Let tc be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with ms, 24
            proc memory_set_int64 from Memory with ms, 24, tc minus 1
            If new_cnt is equal to 0:
                Let nx be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with cur, 16
                If prev is equal to 0:
                    proc memory_set_int64 from Memory with head_addr, 0, nx
                Otherwise:
                    proc memory_set_int64 from Memory with prev, 16, nx
                End If
                proc deallocate from Layout with cur
                Let dc be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with ms, 16
                proc memory_set_int64 from Memory with ms, 16, dc minus 1
            End If
            Return 1
        End If
        Set prev to cur
        Set cur to proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with cur, 16
    End While
    Return 0
End Process

@Reasoning
Total count (sum of all multiplicities).
@End Reasoning

@Implementation
Read total_count at offset 24.
@End Implementation

@Performance_Hints
Time: O(1).
@End Performance_Hints

@Security_Scope
Read-only.
@End Security_Scope
Process called "mset_size" takes ms as Integer returns Integer:
    If ms is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    Return proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with ms, 24
End Process

@Reasoning
Distinct value count.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation
Read distinct_count at offset 16.
@End Implementation

@Performance_Hints
Time: O(1).
@End Performance_Hints

@Security_Scope
Read-only.
@End Security_Scope
Process called "mset_distinct_count" takes ms as Integer returns Integer:
    If ms is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    Return proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with ms, 16
End Process

@Reasoning
Containment predicate.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation
Returns 1 if count > 0.
@End Implementation

@Performance_Hints
Time: O(1) average.
@End Performance_Hints

@Security_Scope
Read-only.
@End Security_Scope
Process called "mset_contains" takes ms as Integer, value as Integer returns Integer:
    If ms is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    Let c be proc mset_count with ms, value
    If c is greater than 0:
        Return 1
    End If
    Return 0
End Process
